DOE Rescinds “Mass Filer” Rule, Reopening Door for Web Accessibility Complaints | Digital Accessibility Committee | University of Illinois at Chicago                        Skip to the content of this page ,  the main menu , the site search form , the site home page .        UIC Logo        Digital Accessibility Committee     Search the site     Toggle Menu      Search                  UIC Logo          Digital Accessibility Committee      Digital Accessibility Committee   Main Menu    Red Accessibility    Resources and Tools    Expand Resources and Tools menu           Non-HTML Content    Online Resources    Tools    Captioning at UIC         Contact Us    Expand Contact Us menu           About the Digital Accessibility Committee          Eyebrow menu    Office for Access and Equity    Disability Resource Center    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map       Search                       DOE Rescinds “Mass Filer” Rule, Reopening Door for Web Accessibility Complaints    Posted on December 13, 2018    In late November, the Department of Education (DOE) Office for Civil Rights (OCR) released a revised Case Processing Manual that reversed controversial rules changes made in March 2018 that automatically dismissed complaints from individuals and organizations that filed multiple complaints. As a result of the rescission of the so-called “Mass Filer” rule, web accessibility complaints against educational institutions are likely to increase significantly.  For more information on this go to the article by C.P. Hoffman,  DOE Rescinds “Mass Filer” Rule, Reopening Door for Web Accessibility Complaints, on the Level Access Web s ite.                   UIC Logo        Digital Accessibility Committee       Contact   Phone: (312) 413-0886  dag@listserv.uic.edu        Social Media Accounts            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC